column12: SYSTEMS AND METHODS FOR AN ONLINE MEDICAL PANEL
column13: In accordance with some embodiments, systems and methods provide for generating a panel of medical experts for a patient being treated by a treating physician who has been diagnosed with a medical condition, the panel of medical experts providing in a timely manner recommendations for a treatment plan for the patient's medical condition. In accordance with some embodiments, the treating physician submits an Opinion Request to an automated service that selects the panel of medical experts, the treating physician providing a narrative of the relevant medical history of the patient and relevant medical images for review by the panel. In accordance with some embodiments, a resultant report of the treatment recommendations from the panel is provided to the treating physician for dissemination to the patient.

column12: SYSTEMS AND METHODS FOR AN EXCLUSIVE ONLINE MEDICAL PANEL
column13: A system, method, and computer program may provide second opinions from live, highly qualified medical experts to a treating physician or patient without needing to schedule appointments, travel to visits, and waste time seeking the second opinions. The method can include (i) forwarding information, based on patient data, to a panel of medical experts, each medical expert chosen according to a rating system; (iv) receive, from each of the medical experts, a recommended treatment option for the medical condition as it applies to the patient based on the information, thereby receiving a plurality of recommendations from the panel; and (v) generating a report for the treating physician, the report summarizing the recommendations.

column12: Modified t lymphocytes and uses therefor
column13: Modified T lymphocytes that express a chimeric T cell receptor reactive with two or more different cell surface angiogenic marker are disclosed. The modified T lymphocytes are useful in methods in controlling angiogenesis and in therapeutic methods in controlling tumor growth.
